Beijing to curb big commercial complexes - paper . The Beijing city government will restrict construction of new commercial complexes , the Market Daily said on Monday . The newspaper , published by the official People ' s Daily , quoted city planners as saying they might halt some projects already approved but where construction had not yet begun . Future approvals of new projects also would be screened closely , it said . The Chinese capital now has 65 such large commercial centres either completed or under construction . Work began on 17 of them last year , the newspaper said . Beijing ' s existing shopping centres have complained of intensifying competition over the past year . Tianqiao Department Store , Beijing Wangfujing Department Store Co and Beijing Xidan Market Co Ltd are among the listed department store operators . All of their shares trade on the Shanghai stock exchange . - - Beijing newsroom ( 8610 ) 65321921 
